Due to the impact of Hurricane Isaias, the Mullica Township Board of Education meeting originally scheduled for August 5th has been rescheduled for Friday, August 7th at 6:30pm.

post_text:
The Mullica Township Education Association is so HAPPY to report that our LIP SYNC BATTLE to raise money for our MTEA Scholarship Fund is SOLD OUT!
All ticket money received by this morning has been processed. Teachers will send home all tickets with students at dismissal. All tickets sold have been recorded by name...so if your student turned in monies - you will have a ticket coming to you.
Unfortunately NO TICKETS will be sold at the door, and we cannot maintain a wait list.
We are thankful for the support of our students and families. Due to our success - we will look to move this event to a larger venue in the future.
Looking forward to “breaking a leg” for our kids!

Barbara Rheault
MTEA President
